1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 28=

3
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:17,280
Dad.

4
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:19,360
She fell asleep.

5
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,822
I went to fetch some hot water.

6
00:02:34,888 --> 00:02:37,155
(Oncology Department)
You stayed with Mom for so long.

7
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,960
What did you talk about?

8
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,480
Just old memories.

9
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,640
A few old friends

10
00:02:43,955 --> 00:02:45,866
got back in touch with me recently.

11
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,560
Why is it only
after she got seriously sick,

12
00:02:53,288 --> 00:02:55,422
that you're willing to stay by her side?

13
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,640
Even though
we weren't living together before,

14
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,680
and lived a bit far apart,

15
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:03,760
your mom knew

16
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,040
I was still there for her.

17
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,320
She knew where to find me.

18
00:03:09,933 --> 00:03:11,688
And she knew if anything happened,

19
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,200
she could call me anytime for help.

20
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,360
Your mom and I
have different ways of living.

21
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,200
I like being alone.

22
00:03:20,911 --> 00:03:22,377
But I was always there.

23
00:03:22,777 --> 00:03:24,244
And she knew that, too.

24
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,720
Now that she has fallen sick,

25
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,311
she can't come looking for me.

26
00:03:30,955 --> 00:03:32,680
This morning, when I heard her talking,

27
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,120
she sounded so weak.

28
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:37,320
So...

29
00:03:38,644 --> 00:03:40,333
I need to stay closer to her now.

30
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,240
If...

31
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,480
the one who got sick had been me,

32
00:03:48,022 --> 00:03:49,466
I would've moved back, too.

33
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,000
So you

34
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:58,040
have actually always cared about her,
right?

35
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:01,520
But I could never care for her
in the way she wanted.

36
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,840
Before this, I honestly thought

37
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,360
you didn't like her.

38
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,360
Once I married your mom,

39
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,120
I never thought about anyone else

40
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,040
for the rest of my life.

41
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,320
Ladies, you're not coming home
for dinner?

42
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,360
Why are you here?

43
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:04,600
Just you alone?

44
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,755
I sent them a message just now.
None of them is coming back for dinner.

45
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:09,360
Can I come in?

46
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,680
Just milk?

47
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,666
Come, eat something.

48
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:17,755
Why did you suddenly come by?

49
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,600
Something happened

50
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,280
at Chenxing, right?

51
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,400
You work in renovations.
How would you know that?

52
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:29,520
You work at that company.
Of course I pay attention.

53
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,400
And Lin Zhanqiao

54
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,240
is someone I should care about, too.

55
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,520
Still haven't found yourself
a new girlfriend?

56
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:44,920
Haven't met the right one.

57
00:05:45,822 --> 00:05:46,840
I'm getting older now.

58
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:47,960
Got to be more picky,

59
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:48,920
right?

60
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,360
What have you heard

61
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:52,600
about Chenxing?

62
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,920
When a small company runs into trouble,

63
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:02,560
it's always about money.

64
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,360
So this time,

65
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,760
I came to tell Lin Zhanqiao

66
00:06:09,288 --> 00:06:10,844
that if there's anything I can do,

67
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,080
I'd like to help.

68
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:14,280
Of course, I can't do anything huge.

69
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,960
I can invest some money.

70
00:06:30,844 --> 00:06:32,644
I don't think she would accept it.

71
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,640
She helps you.

72
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,760
I help you.

73
00:06:37,244 --> 00:06:38,440
Nothing wrong with that.

74
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,800
Life is just people

75
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,800
helping each other out.

76
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,360
Look at me. My business got this big,

77
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,960
and I'm always willing
to help others.

78
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:51,240
And I'm not afraid to ask others
for help either.

79
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:52,920
Ms. Lin isn't like you.

80
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,040
Ask her when she gets back then.

81
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,560
No need to ask her.

82
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,680
She won't accept it.

83
00:07:02,133 --> 00:07:04,066
Whether she accepts it or not
is up to her.

84
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:05,880
But shouldn't we

85
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:07,160
at least show our sincerity?

86
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:10,955
Even if she refuses,

87
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:14,440
she should still know

88
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:17,280
there are people willing to help her
and support her.

89
00:07:18,244 --> 00:07:20,240
Wouldn't that make her feel
a little better?

90
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:24,200
That's true.

91
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,400
Madam,

92
00:07:26,511 --> 00:07:28,160
please have some time.
Just wait a moment.

93
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:28,900
He'll be here soon.

94
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,800
Alright, thank you.

95
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:45,440
Hello, madam.

96
00:07:46,066 --> 00:07:47,120
I'm Zhou Mei's coworker.

97
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,520
Tim had to leave early.

98
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,360
Here's your thing.

99
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:50,240
Okay.

100
00:07:52,111 --> 00:07:53,866
Please check if anything's missing.

101
00:07:57,155 --> 00:07:58,080
This is all I need.

102
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:58,960
Thank you.

103
00:07:58,977 --> 00:07:59,720
You're welcome.

104
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:00,840
I'll walk you out.

105
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,160
No, thanks.

106
00:08:02,911 --> 00:08:04,640
It's fine. I happen
to be heading out, too.

107
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:05,844
We're on the way. Let's go.

108
00:08:05,866 --> 00:08:06,240
Alright.

109
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:06,560
Please.

110
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,560
Madam,

111
00:08:11,022 --> 00:08:13,044
is Mei finally getting
some good news soon?

112
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,080
What good news?

113
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:17,040
Her good news with Lawyer Bei.

114
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,400
She finally got her happy ending
after waiting for so long.

115
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:21,760
What...

116
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,320
What are you talking about?

117
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,240
Is she going to

118
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,560
marry Lawyer Bei?

119
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:27,960
Yeah.

120
00:08:31,755 --> 00:08:33,110
Are you worried people will talk

121
00:08:33,133 --> 00:08:35,640
because Lawyer Bei just got divorced
and is going to remarry?

122
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,800
Honestly, younger generations

123
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,133
don't care about that anymore.

124
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,440
We all know

125
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:43,000
Zhou Mei waited for him for so long.

126
00:08:43,111 --> 00:08:44,320
It really wasn't easy for her.

127
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,480
You go ahead first.

128
00:08:49,711 --> 00:08:50,880
I need to use the restroom.

129
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:51,960
Okay.

130
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,080
Hello, Mom?

131
00:09:05,888 --> 00:09:07,200
Did Tim give you the document?

132
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:11,680
A female coworker?

133
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,920
Is Lawyer Bei the man
who came to our house with you

134
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,120
last time?

135
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,520
What is your relationship with him?

136
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:23,066
Why aren't you saying anything?

137
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,480
Where are you right now?

138
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,240
Are you with a client?

139
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,711
Well, come home tonight.

140
00:09:31,822 --> 00:09:33,320
I'll wait for you at your place.

141
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,760
Send it to this address.

142
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:54,680
Alright.

143
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,200
Here's your receipt.

144
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,760
The total is 2,888 yuan.

145
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,355
Put it inside.

146
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:02,240
Okay.

147
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,280
Thank you.

148
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,600
How long have you known him?

149
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:00,640
A few years.

150
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,320
When you met him,

151
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,040
did you know he was married

152
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:05,920
and had a wife?

153
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:09,040
Yes.

154
00:11:09,422 --> 00:11:11,355
And you still got involved with him?

155
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,520
I wanted him to divorce his wife
and marry me.

156
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:22,400
Do you realize

157
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:23,480
what you just said

158
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,333
is the most shameless thing
in the world?

159
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,800
Have you forgotten

160
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,080
what kind of person

161
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:31,111
caused all the misery in our family?

162
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:36,520
Of course I remember.

163
00:11:40,222 --> 00:11:42,280
Nothing left a deeper impression on me
than that.

164
00:11:47,733 --> 00:11:48,880
When you went to confront my dad

165
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,160
and that mistress,

166
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:52,840
you took me with you.

167
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:56,040
Why did you take me there?

168
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:58,800
Could I help you fight her?

169
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,360
Or could I help you win Dad back?

170
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,400
If not,

171
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,680
then why did you take me?

172
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,560
I wanted you to see

173
00:12:05,688 --> 00:12:07,720
what the ugliest thing in this world
looks like!

174
00:12:08,022 --> 00:12:10,333
What the most shameless kind of person
looks like!

175
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:12,680
I wanted you to see it as a warning!

176
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,640
So you would never choose
a man like that,

177
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:17,520
and never become a woman like that!

178
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,960
You were just trying
to cover up your own cowardice.

179
00:12:23,066 --> 00:12:24,120
You should've fought for

180
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,240
your own husband yourself.

181
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:29,200
You didn't dare beat that woman.

182
00:12:30,133 --> 00:12:32,777
Instead, you forced me to stand there
and watch them together.

183
00:12:32,844 --> 00:12:34,288
What did I even understand back then?

184
00:12:34,844 --> 00:12:36,755
Dad was yelling at you
to take me away.

185
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:38,355
Even that woman
was telling you to leave.

186
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:40,440
But did you ever care about how I felt?

187
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,920
I was a victim, too.

188
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,440
I had nobody else around me

189
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:46,840
but you.

190
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:48,840
And for all these years,

191
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:53,400
you kept dumping your anger and fear

192
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,440
onto me.

193
00:12:54,822 --> 00:12:56,200
Did you think that meant you won?

194
00:12:56,577 --> 00:12:58,755
Did you think that meant
you beat those women?

195
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:00,440
Listen. You didn't.

196
00:13:12,244 --> 00:13:13,422
I bought these clothes

197
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,280
to deal with you.

198
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:18,080
I would never wear clothes
this old-fashioned.

199
00:13:19,266 --> 00:13:21,444
Do you know why I stayed
at Lin Zhanqiao's place?

200
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,880
You think it's closer to work?

201
00:13:23,755 --> 00:13:25,440
It's because everything I use and wear

202
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,520
is over there!

203
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,840
I only keep this house to deal with you!

204
00:13:31,311 --> 00:13:32,800
Don't you think this place feels cheap

205
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,000
and hasn't changed at all?

206
00:13:35,355 --> 00:13:37,133
You've lost your mind, Zhou Mei.

207
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:40,400
You're not my daughter.

208
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,280
You made me become this way.

209
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:47,320
Why are you doing this?

210
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:49,280
Do you mean to torture me?

211
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:51,400
Doesn't this

212
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,360
hurt you?

213
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,200
No.

214
00:13:57,066 --> 00:13:58,630
What hurts is dressing
like this every day,

215
00:13:58,644 --> 00:14:01,333
pretending to be the obedient,
sensible daughter you wanted.

216
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,520
Deep down,

217
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:06,400
you must despise yourself!

218
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,120
I don't!

219
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,360
I'm the winner!

220
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,080
I won against your control.

221
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:15,640
And I won against

222
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:16,600
that woman, too.

223
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,480
You lost, didn't you?

224
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,160
I don't have a daughter like you.

225
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,720
Then you have nothing left at all.

226
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:41,750
♪First time in love♪

227
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:47,370
♪It tears my heart apart♪

228
00:14:49,620 --> 00:14:52,930
♪Keep chasing all♪

229
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:53,960
(Deep love)

230
00:14:54,511 --> 00:14:56,200
(often comes with harsh expectations.)

231
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:59,040
(Beneath Zhou Mei's breakdown)

232
00:14:59,644 --> 00:15:00,680
(is anger at herself)

233
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:03,000
(for being unable to mend
the relationship with her mother)

234
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,080
(and also a desperate cry)

235
00:15:06,644 --> 00:15:08,920
(to free both herself and her mother
from resentment.)

236
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:13,160
(For some reason,)

237
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:17,240
(we always hurt
the people closest to us the most)

238
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,360
(with cruel words without thinking,)

239
00:15:21,755 --> 00:15:23,240
(and then spend the rest of the time)

240
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,400
(regretting them.)

241
00:15:27,870 --> 00:15:31,880
♪I see you at the end♪

242
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:37,210
♪Now I cross the line♪

243
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,400
You're here.

244
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:49,440
Are you alright?

245
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:50,200
I'm fine.

246
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:58,560
Too bad I didn't keep liquor at home.

247
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:00,640
But today,

248
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:01,840
we have to drink.

249
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,133
Guess we'll drink this instead.

250
00:16:05,533 --> 00:16:07,400
Ten-year aged
scallion-ginger cooking liquor.

251
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:09,320
Sure.

252
00:16:09,911 --> 00:16:11,066
Never tried it before.

253
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:11,960
Give it a taste.

254
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:23,240
Here.

255
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:35,160
How is it?

256
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:37,800
Nice.

257
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,840
As expected of ten-year aged brew.

258
00:16:41,155 --> 00:16:42,080
The aroma is intense.

259
00:16:58,400 --> 00:16:59,680
You and Lawyer Bei

260
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,320
were never talking about marriage.

261
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:06,520
He didn't divorce his wife

262
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:07,840
because you forced him to.

263
00:17:08,644 --> 00:17:11,280
Why did you have to act like
you had done every terrible thing

264
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:13,000
in front of your mom?

265
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:16,644
To get back at her.

266
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,040
Actually, I was on edge

267
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:21,480
before I talked to her.

268
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,440
But when I faced her head-on

269
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,080
and saw how upset she was,

270
00:17:26,177 --> 00:17:27,755
I suddenly stopped feeling nervous.

271
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:30,040
I had finally

272
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:31,600
waited long enough for this day.

273
00:17:32,133 --> 00:17:33,666
I finally became myself again.

274
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:37,360
Congrats.

275
00:17:37,977 --> 00:17:39,311
On becoming yourself again.

276
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,400
May it inspire you, too.

277
00:17:47,177 --> 00:17:49,200
When will you become
your real self again?

278
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:52,280
I've always been myself.

279
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:53,440
Stop lying to yourself.

280
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:55,680
You're drunk.

281
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,880
The moment you tell He Han

282
00:17:58,280 --> 00:17:59,440
that you like him,

283
00:17:59,555 --> 00:18:01,090
no matter how badly he has treated you,

284
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:03,155
that's when you'll finally
be honest with yourself.

285
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,320
Jeez.

286
00:18:10,888 --> 00:18:11,977
Total lovesick idiot.

287
00:18:12,488 --> 00:18:13,760
You do like him. That's a fact.

288
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,680
You can reject all his ridiculous logic,

289
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:18,440
say he's unreliable,

290
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:20,200
say you don't want to work with him,

291
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,240
or live with him.

292
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:23,320
But you can't deny

293
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:24,600
that you like him.

294
00:18:26,844 --> 00:18:28,320
What's the point of liking someone?

295
00:18:28,320 --> 00:18:29,844
Can it put food on the table?

296
00:18:30,222 --> 00:18:31,240
All it brings is pain.

297
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:37,960
You're scared

298
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,266
you'll end up like your mom,

299
00:18:39,355 --> 00:18:40,840
spending your whole life loving a man,

300
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,520
only to be pushed far away in the end.

301
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,840
I won't become my mom.

302
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,160
She has suffered too much.

303
00:18:55,622 --> 00:18:56,777
They've been married

304
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,120
for decades.

305
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:00,840
Now that I'm grown up,

306
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,120
she still can't get close to my dad.

307
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:11,320
If I ever like someone,

308
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:15,600
I'll definitely stay by his side.

309
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:17,760
Very close.

310
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:19,600
Very close.

311
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:32,360
Come.

312
00:19:58,600 --> 00:19:59,040
Mr. Lin.

313
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:02,480
You've terminated
the lease on your place?

314
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:03,640
I have.

315
00:20:06,222 --> 00:20:07,520
I know what you're trying to ask.

316
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,040
You're wondering what if I move back in

317
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:11,640
and can't get used to it anymore, right?

318
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,640
You've lived alone

319
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,080
for over twenty years.

320
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,480
Of course I won't be used to it.

321
00:20:18,577 --> 00:20:19,866
I'll just have to put up with it.

322
00:20:19,933 --> 00:20:21,822
Young people call it
"try and work it through"?

323
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:23,160
But honestly,

324
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,400
compared to most people,

325
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,240
I had an extra

326
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:26,920
twenty years of freedom.

327
00:20:27,266 --> 00:20:28,240
I'm satisfied with that.

328
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:30,560
I always knew

329
00:20:30,711 --> 00:20:32,666
one day I would have to move back.

330
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:34,200
I told Zhanqiao, too.

331
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:36,600
Whether her mom gets sick

332
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:37,400
or I do,

333
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:39,240
once that day comes, I'll move back.

334
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:42,560
No matter what,

335
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,560
you keep your word.

336
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:45,000
I really admire you for that.

337
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,560
Freedom always comes at a price.

338
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,160
Either you pay for it yourself,

339
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,360
or someone else pays for it for you.

340
00:20:58,240 --> 00:21:00,320
Maybe Mrs. Lin doesn't resent you
that much.

341
00:21:02,088 --> 00:21:03,320
It's not just Zhanqiao's mom.

342
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,920
Zhanqiao paid the price, too.

343
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:09,960
When parents can't even
get along normally,

344
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:12,680
do you think
the child doesn't suffer for it?

345
00:21:13,888 --> 00:21:15,800
People always say
children learn by example.

346
00:21:15,933 --> 00:21:17,333
She never had a good example.

347
00:21:17,422 --> 00:21:18,933
All she learned were the bad parts.

348
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:20,720
That's why she can't properly

349
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:22,480
get along with you now.

350
00:21:22,533 --> 00:21:24,400
No. That's because
I'm hard to get along with.

351
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,000
Not you. Zhanqiao is.

352
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:27,560
How could that be?

353
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:29,080
It has to be me.

354
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:30,622
No. She's the one with the problem.

355
00:21:30,688 --> 00:21:32,600
She's my daughter.
Wouldn't I know her best?

356
00:21:47,420 --> 00:21:48,760
(Exclusive Licensing Agreement
[Draft Termination Agreement])

357
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:49,920
(Proof of Contract Breach)
Hello, Ms. Lin.

358
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:51,760
I'm Mr. Wang Hai's attorney.

359
00:21:52,733 --> 00:21:53,640
(Confidentiality Agreement)
You should know

360
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,911
that Mr. Wang Hai
is a contracted author under Chenxing.

361
00:21:56,044 --> 00:21:56,950
Based on what we've learned,

362
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:58,000
during your collaboration,

363
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:00,520
Chenxing committed multiple
breaches of contract.

364
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:02,120
That has led my client,

365
00:22:02,222 --> 00:22:04,666
Mr. Wang Hai, to consider
terminating the agreement.

366
00:22:04,955 --> 00:22:06,200
(Demand Letter)
I'm meeting you

367
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:09,400
to discuss the matters
related to the termination.

368
00:22:10,911 --> 00:22:12,244
There's an agreement here.

369
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:13,488
Please take a look.

370
00:22:21,266 --> 00:22:22,920
Have you read these agreements yourself?

371
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:26,560
No.

372
00:22:27,444 --> 00:22:29,911
But I know Dingqi was going
to approach you.

373
00:22:30,760 --> 00:22:32,200
I know Mr. Fan and Zhao Lanxin

374
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:33,720
can give you a very good offer.

375
00:22:34,066 --> 00:22:36,666
But at a time like this, hearing you
bring up termination with me,

376
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:37,520
that really hurts.

377
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:41,200
Mr. Fan said

378
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,480
they'll give you
the compensation you deserve.

379
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:46,200
You can take the money

380
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,520
and find a better author.

381
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,640
I thought our partnership

382
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:51,000
meant more

383
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,680
than just money.

384
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,080
Between us,

385
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:57,040
it's work and business.

386
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:58,760
It's all about money.

387
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,320
Or mostly about money.

388
00:23:02,066 --> 00:23:03,444
Now that I've accepted that,

389
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:06,022
but you're turning around and telling me

390
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:08,377
not to talk money with you?

391
00:23:09,177 --> 00:23:10,640
When it comes to work and business,

392
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:13,240
shouldn't people go

393
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:15,822
wherever gives them better opportunities
and a better future?

394
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:19,200
In the short term,

395
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:21,040
I do think Dingqi can give you

396
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:22,600
more exposure, more opportunities,

397
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:24,311
maybe even a higher revenue split.

398
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:26,680
But in the long run,

399
00:23:26,844 --> 00:23:28,800
Zhao Lanxin won't be able
to help your writing

400
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:29,840
that much.

401
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:31,720
Nobody can predict the long term.

402
00:23:32,044 --> 00:23:33,960
Back when I worked as
an internet cafe manager,

403
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:34,960
I never imagined

404
00:23:35,088 --> 00:23:37,511
that one day I would be
writing novels with you.

405
00:23:37,688 --> 00:23:38,880
And after I started writing,

406
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:41,355
I never imagined I'd rise
to the top so quickly.

407
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:43,440
But what I never expected most

408
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:47,711
was that I still wouldn't
get the recognition I wanted.

409
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:51,120
Authors go through

410
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:52,840
highs and lows.

411
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,800
Zhao Lanxin won't patiently wait for you
through those lows.

412
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:59,410
The moment someone else
can bring her more profit,

413
00:23:59,422 --> 00:24:00,520
she'll move on to them.

414
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:01,520
She will.

415
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,320
Even on her wedding day,

416
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,022
she was still asking about my life!

417
00:24:05,066 --> 00:24:06,040
As long as I need her,

418
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:07,240
she'll come see me anytime.

419
00:24:07,370 --> 00:24:09,720
When I was writing the sequel to
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui,

420
00:24:09,733 --> 00:24:11,488
she stayed up with me
night after night,

421
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:12,920
waiting for my updates.

422
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:13,800
She told me

423
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:16,040
I was the best author
she had ever worked with.

424
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:25,800
Maybe she can't help me
write better stories,

425
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:29,080
but she makes me

426
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,440
feel valued,

427
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,040
needed.

428
00:24:38,080 --> 00:24:39,360
If that's what you want,

429
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:40,960
I'm sorry,

430
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:42,640
I can't give you that.

431
00:24:47,440 --> 00:24:48,240
One more thing.

432
00:24:49,466 --> 00:24:50,800
During the call with the lawyer,

433
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:53,200
he brought up details
from our past collaboration.

434
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:55,560
Like payments being delayed by two days.

435
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:58,120
Or disagreements over progress.

436
00:24:59,444 --> 00:25:00,977
Did you tell Dingqi

437
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:03,160
about all that?

438
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:03,600
No.

439
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:05,111
I didn't say anything.

440
00:25:06,520 --> 00:25:07,200
Mr. Fan said

441
00:25:07,577 --> 00:25:09,080
they have an insider at Chenxing.

442
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:11,600
Alright.

443
00:25:12,666 --> 00:25:13,955
As for the termination,

444
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,760
let the lawyers handle it.

445
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:20,200
I'll finish writing Drunk Old Friend.

446
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:23,640
Finish it well.

447
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:24,120
It's good

448
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:24,880
for you

449
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:25,960
and me.

450
00:25:58,444 --> 00:25:59,800
Where are you, Ms. Zhao?

451
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:02,800
The cervical cyst surgery itself
is a minor procedure,

452
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,760
and we'll try our best

453
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:05,880
to minimize tissue damage.

454
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:07,440
But I should let you know this.

455
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:09,600
Your cyst is relatively large,

456
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:11,320
and the surgical area will also

457
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,320
be slightly larger.

458
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:13,840
After the removal,

459
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,400
there is a risk of scarring or adhesion,

460
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,577
which could affect your chances
of a natural pregnancy in the future.

461
00:26:18,780 --> 00:26:20,900
(Liu Blind Massage)

462
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:21,320
Hello?

463
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:22,240
Lin Zhanqiao.

464
00:26:23,066 --> 00:26:24,480
I was worried you would be upset,

465
00:26:24,755 --> 00:26:26,666
so I asked Zhangzhu
to pass you a message.

466
00:26:27,360 --> 00:26:28,960
Also, I recently took on a new project.

467
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:30,120
The houses are amazing.

468
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:31,800
Come take a look if you have time.

469
00:26:32,577 --> 00:26:34,540
Doesn't matter if you don't have
money right now.

470
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:36,560
Looking at houses can lift your mood

471
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:38,000
and make you feel like

472
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,560
a new life is waiting for you.

473
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:42,280
Thanks.

474
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,600
If Chenxing goes under,

475
00:26:44,711 --> 00:26:46,533
maybe I'll work for you selling houses.

476
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:48,320
Then I can look at homes
every day

477
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:49,920
and dream about a new life.

478
00:26:59,060 --> 00:27:02,340
(Oncology Department)

479
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:11,160
Bed 31,

480
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,000
you're being discharged today.

481
00:27:13,133 --> 00:27:14,360
Has your family arrived yet?

482
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:16,040
Yes.

483
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:16,560
Mom.

484
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:17,160
Thank you.

485
00:27:17,533 --> 00:27:19,040
Didn't I say I would help you pack?

486
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:20,280
Why did you do it yourself?

487
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:21,840
It's barely anything.

488
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:23,160
No need to trouble you.

489
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:24,960
Give me a moment.

490
00:27:25,088 --> 00:27:26,488
I'm going to make a payment.

491
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:44,560
Hello, Ms. Zhao.

492
00:27:44,733 --> 00:27:46,422
You forgot your medical insurance card.

493
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:47,560
Thank you.

494
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:49,480
Where's your family?

495
00:27:50,066 --> 00:27:52,044
They stepped away. They'll be back soon.

496
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:55,360
Make sure you rest in bed
for a couple of days after you go home.

497
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:53,320
Are you okay?

498
00:28:57,480 --> 00:28:58,800
What a small world.

499
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,360
Do you need any help?

500
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:04,120
You don't look

501
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:05,360
very well.

502
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:07,920
I'm fine. Don't worry about me.

503
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:09,755
I'll just sit here and rest for a bit.

504
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:15,720
How about you wait here for me?

505
00:29:15,977 --> 00:29:17,120
I'll bring my mom downstairs,

506
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:18,333
and then I'll drive you home.

507
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:23,520
Thank you.

508
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:24,800
I'll be quick.

509
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:04,560
Sea cucumber.

510
00:30:05,733 --> 00:30:06,777
Bird's nest soup.

511
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:09,111
Black chicken soup.

512
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:11,280
Fish maw pigeon soup.

513
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:13,080
Dining alone?

514
00:30:13,466 --> 00:30:15,400
Would you like to add
vegetables or staples?

515
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,070
No, that's all.

516
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:17,511
Alright. Please wait a moment.

517
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:25,040
Excuse me, ma'am. Your meal is here.

518
00:30:28,350 --> 00:30:32,250
♪After giving everything, I
couldn't wait any longer♪

519
00:30:35,230 --> 00:30:39,330
♪The verdict was
already waiting in the future♪

520
00:30:41,467 --> 00:30:43,257
♪Why bother confessing♪

521
00:30:43,420 --> 00:30:44,950
♪Or thinking about what to say?♪

522
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:47,300
♪It's none of my concern♪

523
00:30:47,420 --> 00:30:50,220
♪Even if it's unraveled♪

524
00:30:50,500 --> 00:30:52,060
♪It had already fallen apart♪

525
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:54,200
♪Endless dependence♪

526
00:30:54,450 --> 00:30:57,320
♪I really miss♪

527
00:30:57,320 --> 00:31:01,140
♪All the beautiful moments together♪

528
00:31:01,430 --> 00:31:04,310
♪I may seem to be alone♪

529
00:31:04,550 --> 00:31:07,250
♪But I'm still waiting♪

530
00:31:08,490 --> 00:31:11,770
♪Happiness feels like an accident♪

531
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:15,200
♪Why be overly generous♪

532
00:31:15,470 --> 00:31:18,760
♪Beyond the limits of endurance♪

533
00:31:18,990 --> 00:31:22,400
♪Living in humble silence♪

534
00:31:22,660 --> 00:31:25,450
♪Who is it within the crowd♪

535
00:31:25,450 --> 00:31:29,320
♪Gathering strength beneath the waves?♪

536
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:32,600
♪Who wasted their time
waiting for the wrong person♪

537
00:31:32,820 --> 00:31:36,380
♪In despair?♪

538
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:40,230
♪Saving the love you once gave me♪

539
00:31:40,230 --> 00:31:46,900
♪I don't need your pity♪

540
00:32:07,577 --> 00:32:08,760
Why weren't you answering?

541
00:32:08,977 --> 00:32:11,133
I was interviewing editors.
I couldn't take calls.

542
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:13,488
Didn't I come over right away
as soon as I finished?

543
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,440
You don't look quite well.

544
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:17,760
Really?

545
00:32:18,222 --> 00:32:20,088
Maybe I didn't sleep well last night.

546
00:32:20,555 --> 00:32:22,244
What did you want to see me about?

547
00:32:24,066 --> 00:32:26,044
Did Lin Zhanqiao give you trouble again?

548
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:30,640
More like

549
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:33,040
I became her trouble.

550
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:37,800
Between you,

551
00:32:38,355 --> 00:32:40,177
you're the one calling the shots now.

552
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:44,800
Back then, Lin Zhanqiao lost He Han,

553
00:32:45,080 --> 00:32:46,800
and Chenxing fell into
a business crisis.

554
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:48,840
Luckily, she was prepared.

555
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:51,200
She had you to pull her out of the fire.

556
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:53,440
Now she has lost you, too.

557
00:32:54,222 --> 00:32:55,630
No one will save her this time.

558
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,560
I hope the lawyer

559
00:32:57,955 --> 00:33:00,120
won't lower the penalty fee,
no matter the reason.

560
00:33:03,840 --> 00:33:04,960
Her problem now

561
00:33:05,333 --> 00:33:07,755
isn't whether it's five million more
or ten million less.

562
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:09,520
She needs to reflect on herself.

563
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:11,920
She's too proud.

564
00:33:12,088 --> 00:33:14,022
She needs to learn
how to swallow her pride.

565
00:33:14,044 --> 00:33:15,500
But then she wouldn't be
Lin Zhanqiao anymore.

566
00:33:15,510 --> 00:33:16,711
She refuses to bow her head,

567
00:33:16,755 --> 00:33:19,360
so the only thing left
is for setbacks to crush her first.

568
00:33:19,755 --> 00:33:21,733
And when that happens,
it'll only look worse.

569
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,720
If I compensate her more on my side,

570
00:33:23,822 --> 00:33:26,288
it'll only delay the moment
she has to face reality.

571
00:33:28,600 --> 00:33:29,720
She'll talk to you again.

572
00:33:33,222 --> 00:33:35,100
She still has responsibilities
toward Chenxing.

573
00:33:35,266 --> 00:33:37,120
She won't want to disappoint
her employees.

574
00:33:37,955 --> 00:33:39,511
She'll definitely come again

575
00:33:40,266 --> 00:33:41,000
and beg you.

576
00:33:45,111 --> 00:33:46,377
I never imagined it.

577
00:33:48,222 --> 00:33:50,360
Until yesterday,
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui

578
00:33:50,422 --> 00:33:52,160
had been firmly holding
the number one spot.

579
00:33:52,560 --> 00:33:53,640
But one hour after

580
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:55,440
Drunk Old friend updated,

581
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:58,160
its number quickly overtook it.

582
00:33:58,160 --> 00:33:59,420
(Drunk Old Friend,
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

583
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:00,000
Besides,

584
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:03,066
Gu Yan's control over pacing
has improved.

585
00:34:03,177 --> 00:34:04,920
He has started leaving hooks
in the story,

586
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:08,040
getting readers to discuss it
in the comments section.

587
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:10,080
From what I'm seeing so far,

588
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:11,320
all the data

589
00:34:11,577 --> 00:34:12,755
looks extremely strong.

590
00:34:13,320 --> 00:34:15,360
If Sansan really is Gu Yan,

591
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:17,840
then updating two novels
at the same time

592
00:34:18,640 --> 00:34:20,200
was something He Han never managed to do

593
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:22,640
back in the day.

594
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:25,440
The consulting firm we hired

595
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,200
also believes Gu Yan has now entered

596
00:34:27,200 --> 00:34:28,400
a phase of rapid maturity.

597
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:30,040
So they advise us

598
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:32,840
to keep Gu Yan with us, no matter what.

599
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:35,760
Only then will we have leverage

600
00:34:35,844 --> 00:34:37,577
when negotiating with investors.

601
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:46,520
I went to see him.

602
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:51,160
Dingqi gave him extremely good offers.

603
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:53,044
There's no way we can compete.

604
00:34:54,240 --> 00:34:55,720
So the chances of keeping him

605
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:57,680
are small.

606
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:01,440
And if we go by
the breach of contract terms,

607
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:02,800
with his current value,

608
00:35:02,866 --> 00:35:04,666
we would definitely take a huge loss.

609
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:07,680
The main issue now is
he's not even willing to pay

610
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:09,222
the amount stated in the contract.

611
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:11,577
Instead, he's accusing us
of treating him unfairly.

612
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:13,480
I've never seen someone
so ungrateful

613
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,480
and opportunistic.

614
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:15,600
What do you call this?

615
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:16,800
Isn't he a total ingrate?

616
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:17,990
How can someone be like this?

617
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:19,760
- Alright. Enough.
- Ingrate.

618
00:35:19,770 --> 00:35:22,320
Big companies exploit their talent.
Big talents push companies around.

619
00:35:22,333 --> 00:35:23,600
That's how it works everywhere.

620
00:35:23,840 --> 00:35:25,920
It's like agencies managing celebrities.

621
00:35:26,488 --> 00:35:28,960
When you're not famous yet,
you're the one under pressure.

622
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:31,390
But once you become famous,
the company's under pressure instead.

623
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,960
What happened to basic human decency?

624
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:34,520
Tell me about it.

625
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:37,440
That's why
the consulting firm suggested

626
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:39,120
that if things don't work out,

627
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,240
we should compromise

628
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:44,360
and agree to Gu Yan's non-exclusive
open collaboration model.

629
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:47,480
Gu Yan would still maintain
a formal contract with us,

630
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:50,200
but we would allow him

631
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:52,040
to work on other projects with Dingqi.

632
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:53,240
What does that mean?

633
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,040
We worked so hard

634
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:58,240
to develop this author,

635
00:35:58,422 --> 00:36:00,688
and now we have to share him
with someone else?

636
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:02,040
This is humiliating.

637
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:03,400
You think that's humiliating?

638
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:06,066
Gu Yan and Dingqi might not
even be willing to agree to it.

639
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:12,120
This is betrayal.

640
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:13,866
- This is humiliating.
- He might refuse?

641
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:15,933
I've never seen someone like this.

642
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:17,640
He never cared about us.

643
00:36:21,444 --> 00:36:22,680
I'll go talk to him again.

644
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:26,280
What if

645
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:27,680
he still says no?

646
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:29,280
Then I'll beg him.

647
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:30,840
Ask him to help us.

648
00:36:31,133 --> 00:36:32,933
Even if it's for Chenxing's sake.

649
00:36:33,680 --> 00:36:34,120
Ms. Lin,

650
00:36:34,666 --> 00:36:37,333
no matter what, you should
never have to use the word "beg".

651
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:39,560
Without you and Chenxing,

652
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:41,111
he wouldn't be where he is today.

653
00:36:41,840 --> 00:36:42,840
Times have changed.

654
00:36:43,066 --> 00:36:44,355
You adapt to the situation

655
00:36:45,311 --> 00:36:46,511
and bend when you have to bend.

656
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:49,120
- Never seen someone this shameless.
- So frustrating.

657
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:49,800
Jeez.

658
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:53,200
If she begs you,

659
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:54,280
will you soften?

660
00:36:58,044 --> 00:36:58,920
Of course I will.

661
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:00,080
And she knows that, too.

662
00:37:00,844 --> 00:37:02,222
That's exactly why you mustn't.

663
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:06,920
Everything humble she's doing right now

664
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,320
is nothing but an act

665
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:10,755
to get through this rough patch.

666
00:37:11,440 --> 00:37:12,960
At her core,

667
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,780
she's still the high and mighty
Lin Zhanqiao.

668
00:37:15,120 --> 00:37:15,720
To you,

669
00:37:16,120 --> 00:37:16,600
to me,

670
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:19,920
probably to everyone except He Han.

671
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:22,000
The moment you give in,

672
00:37:22,177 --> 00:37:23,800
the moment you give her room to breathe,

673
00:37:24,155 --> 00:37:26,200
she'll immediately go back to
how she used to be.

674
00:37:26,466 --> 00:37:29,244
And you'll go back to being that Gu Yan
buried down in the dirt.

675
00:37:29,288 --> 00:37:30,020
(Phantom Knight)

676
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:32,480
Only if you never compromise
and never back down

677
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:36,520
can you stay in control.

678
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:41,560
You mean

679
00:37:42,080 --> 00:37:43,000
stay in control?

680
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:44,920
I've never thought that way.

681
00:37:45,080 --> 00:37:45,920
You didn't dare to.

682
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:48,040
But I'll show you

683
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:49,200
that you can.

684
00:37:59,822 --> 00:38:00,880
What about you and me?

685
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:02,080
Between us,

686
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:03,200
it's equal.

687
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:06,160
My job is to push you
as high as possible.

688
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:08,440
We rise together.

689
00:38:21,266 --> 00:38:22,422
(Zhanqiao)
She's calling?

690
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:24,080
If she wants to come see you,

691
00:38:24,244 --> 00:38:25,240
tell her to come later.

692
00:38:26,044 --> 00:38:27,400
I'm taking you somewhere first.

693
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:33,600
Hello?

694
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:34,920
Hello?

695
00:38:37,222 --> 00:38:38,777
Do you have time right now?

696
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:39,760
I want to

697
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:42,200
come to your place again.

698
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:43,880
Tomorrow.

699
00:38:44,160 --> 00:38:44,800
I'm busy today.

700
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:06,240
Other than Gu Yan,

701
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,266
pull together the editors

702
00:39:07,270 --> 00:39:09,280
who handle the company's
three best-performing projects.

703
00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:10,560
Set up a meeting this afternoon.

704
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:11,890
I'll oversee it myself.

705
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:12,920
- Okay.
- Understood.

706
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:17,280
Is she trying to create
another Gu Yan overnight?

707
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:18,830
Impossible. There's not enough time.

708
00:39:18,840 --> 00:39:19,440
No way.

709
00:39:20,222 --> 00:39:21,580
What are you guys talking about?

710
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:22,120
Nothing.

711
00:39:22,177 --> 00:39:23,280
Just desperate measures.

712
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:26,920
Thank you.

713
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,280
Where are we going?

714
00:39:28,733 --> 00:39:29,760
To look at a place.

715
00:39:30,155 --> 00:39:32,422
I think you deserve a better environment
for writing.

716
00:39:33,400 --> 00:39:34,080
My place is fine.

717
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:35,400
I live alone.

718
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,577
I don't need that much space.

719
00:39:36,720 --> 00:39:37,680
Take a look first.

720
00:39:38,720 --> 00:39:39,360
Trust me.

721
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:40,360
You'll like it.

722
00:39:59,244 --> 00:40:00,311
What's wrong?

723
00:40:00,777 --> 00:40:02,720
Wasn't this the hotel
He Han used to stay at?

724
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:04,240
That's right.

725
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:06,760
Is this the place

726
00:40:06,888 --> 00:40:07,733
you rent for me?

727
00:40:11,680 --> 00:40:12,360
Hello, Ms. Zhao.

728
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:14,720
Your room is ready.

729
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:17,288
Please come with me.

730
00:40:19,822 --> 00:40:20,720
This way, please.

731
00:40:29,377 --> 00:40:31,422
This is the suite
He Han stayed in before.

732
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:33,360
It's the best room in the hotel.

733
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:36,360
Go in and take a look.

734
00:40:37,733 --> 00:40:38,880
We'll look around ourselves.

735
00:40:38,880 --> 00:40:39,760
Please wait outside.

736
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:40,422
Of course.

737
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:43,160
This suite is over 300 square meters.

738
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:45,422
Temperature-controlled,
humidity-controlled,

739
00:40:45,466 --> 00:40:46,977
fully ventilated, and soundproof.

740
00:40:47,133 --> 00:40:48,120
The living room overlooks

741
00:40:48,120 --> 00:40:49,720
the busiest part of the city.

742
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:53,600
Convenient transportation.
Full facilities nearby.

743
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:57,280
Parks, malls, and stadiums.
Everything you need is here.

744
00:40:57,822 --> 00:41:00,200
And most importantly,
the restaurant here is excellent.

745
00:41:01,080 --> 00:41:03,080
This is the perfect environment
for writing.

746
00:41:04,133 --> 00:41:05,311
Go take a look at the bedroom.

747
00:41:05,555 --> 00:41:06,800
I don't want to stay here.

748
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:09,160
Why not?

749
00:41:12,622 --> 00:41:13,800
It reminds me of He Han.

750
00:41:14,044 --> 00:41:15,720
That means you still can't get past him.

751
00:41:16,488 --> 00:41:18,040
Even though he has stopped writing,

752
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:20,320
you still feel inferior to him.

753
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:24,840
I want you to move in here

754
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:26,240
so you can see

755
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:28,760
that you've completely replaced him.

756
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,840
When this place slowly becomes yours,

757
00:41:32,560 --> 00:41:33,720
when you sleep in that bed

758
00:41:33,777 --> 00:41:35,200
without thinking about him anymore,

759
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:38,560
then whether you face
Lin Zhanqiao or He Han,

760
00:41:38,933 --> 00:41:39,880
you'll finally feel

761
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:42,560
that you deserve the best treatment
and the highest respect.

762
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:44,520
Of course,

763
00:41:45,120 --> 00:41:45,920
having you live here

764
00:41:46,066 --> 00:41:47,688
is also a way of telling everyone else

765
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:49,720
that you've replaced He Han.

766
00:41:53,777 --> 00:41:54,755
Please come in.

767
00:41:55,120 --> 00:41:56,800
The manager heard you might move in,

768
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:58,400
so they specially prepared

769
00:41:58,511 --> 00:42:00,370
the hotel's signature afternoon tea
for you.

770
00:42:04,720 --> 00:42:05,840
One wine glass is enough.

771
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:06,870
I should get going.

772
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:08,022
I'm not drinking today.

773
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:09,800
When you move in,

774
00:42:10,040 --> 00:42:11,400
I'll celebrate with you then.

775
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:13,560
You can leave whenever you want.

776
00:42:13,933 --> 00:42:15,520
If you decide to move in, let me know.

777
00:42:20,200 --> 00:42:21,088
Oh, right.

778
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:23,280
The building across from these windows

779
00:42:23,680 --> 00:42:25,040
is Lin Zhanqiao's office.

780
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:27,320
He Han probably stayed here

781
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:29,040
because of that.

782
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

783
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

784
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

785
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

786
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

787
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

788
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

789
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

790
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

791
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

792
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

793
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

794
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

795
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

796
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

797
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

798
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

799
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

800
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

801
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

802
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

803
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

804
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

805
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

806
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

807
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

808
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

809
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

810
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

811
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

812
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

813
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

814
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

815
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

816
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

817
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

818
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪

